backgroundSnippet:
Poor sleep is prevalent in those with inflammatory bowel disease (IBD), with benzodiazepines often used although not recommended 
for management of insomnia. This study aimed to characterise benzodiazepine use within an IBD population and it’s associations with sleep quality, 
co-morbid depression/anxiety and health status.

Ulcerative colitis (UC) is a chronic relapsing inflammatory disease affecting the large bowel. There is an increasing incidence and prev­
alence in Asian countries, with a shift towards younger patients in high income regions. More than half of UC patients present with moderate disease; 
despite this, studies have suggested a less than 2% use of advanced therapies (AT).
